<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-08-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-08-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="286" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d286">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.77/150</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Francis</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Petrograd</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-08-13"><hi rend="italic">August 13,
                                        1917</hi></date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received August
                                        18, 4.50 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1624. [For] <persName corresp="#p_WD1">Willard</persName> [from
                                    <persName corresp="#p_SJF1">Stevens</persName>]:</p>
                            <p>Spare parts for all new decapods should come with these decapods,
                                those most important first. <persName>Schulenberg</persName><note n="2" xml:id="d286fn2">Russian purchasing agents in the United
                                    States.</note> and Lipets<note n="2" xml:id="d286fn3">Russian
                                    purchasing agents in the United States.</note> should so
                                arrange. Where are the 375 decapods on old Russian order? They were
                                to have been ready for Shop delivery last April. Cable quick if any
                                have been shipped from Pacific ports and about when such shipment
                                will be completed.</p>
                            <closer>[<signed><persName corresp="#p_FDR1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Francis</hi></persName></signed>]</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>